description: 1985 PORSCHE 911 CARRERA TARGA
--Silver Metallic with Black leather, Black carpeting and Black targa top, 61,000 miles, 3.2 liter, 6 cylinder with a 5-Speed Manual Transmission.

The Carrera 3.2 is admired as the pinnacle development of the original 911 that first appeared in 1963. These final G-Series cars replaced the SC Series cars in 1984. They were the last of the original Porsche 911 design before the 964 bodies launched in 1990. The all-alloy, flat-6 engine gave the 911 231hp, which meant a 0-60 time of 5.5 seconds. All Carrera 3.2's feature galvanized bodies, which ensure that these classics are long lasting.

This 1985 Porsche 911 Carrera 3.2 Targa has benefited from proper maintenance and care from Autosport Designs, Inc. and has only covered just over 61,000 miles from new. It was also previously sold by Autosport Designs, Inc. and has benefited from long-term ownership. The 915 transmission shifts very well and the 911 drives very smoothly. The radio has been upgraded to an Alpine unit.
This 911 Carrera 3.2 Targa comes with its original books and tools and is perfect for any collection, Porsche or otherwise.
Up for sale is a stunning 1984 Porsche 911 Targa with just 37251 original documented miles.
Aircooled 911s are harder and harder to come by, especially with low miles like this one!
This absolute rust and accident free Targa comes with a clean carfax history report which documents the accuracy of the extreme low mileage and shows no indication of any accidents or damage.
The Porsche spent all its life in warm climate. Before it came to California in 2009 it was located in the sunshine state of Florida.
As mentioned before: It is absolutely rust free and has no acid damage in the battery compartment!
This car looks stunning inside and out and only shows minimal signs of wear.
Please take a look at all the detailed pictures and judge by yourself. Leather, seats, carpets and door panels have been professionally redone a few years ago.
All body panels are laser straight with even gaps. The car runs absolutely fantastic with no known issues or any kind of fluid leaks.
The Porsche has just undergone a complete service including a transmission rebuild. The work was performed by one of San Diego's most well known independent Porsche mechanics.
It comes with all original books, keys and tons of service records.
If you are in the market for a low mileage, well maintained aircooled 911 - this might be the one for you!

1984 Porsche 911 Red Over Black

Finished in elegant and sporting Guards Red with a black leather interior and black top, this outstanding 911 convertible features:  3.2 liter horizontally opposed 6-cylinder, 5-speed manual transmission and under 46,000 original miles. Spent over a year locating the perfect 911, which in my opinion, is a numbers-matching Carrera with original paint and a clean history. Reason for selling: moving. Purchased in 2011, with 43,623 miles, from Classic Car Studio's Noah Alexander, in St. Louis, who now has a TV show SPEED IS THE NEW BLACK.  Clean Carfax. This car was federalized when it first arrived in the US and received smog equipment, front reflectors, and a MPH speedometer, but still retains unique European details, including side indicator repeaters, smaller rear bumperettes, the more powerful Euro motor, the small lower brake light and Euro Hella H4 headlights. The car makes 231 HP compared to its US counterpart with 214 HP.  Wonderful original condition. Fully galvanized body, AC system, and highly reliable. Some wear to leather seats and door panels. Dash and carpet look great for age. German canvas top in good condition except tears in plastic windows on both sides. Paint is excellent with minor stone chips on front hood and a great luster and shine. Garaged in climate controlled environment since purchase and only driven in good weather. Replaced battery with new one with permanent trickle-charger hook-up. Replaced tires and added cloth cover and reproduction owner's manual.   Race-bred handling, compelling color, competent performance; iconic air-cooled.
